        "title": "fix(search): enforce native web search tool policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nEnforce effective OpenClaw tool policy before enabling provider-native Codex/OpenAI `web_search`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Gate Codex native web-search activation with the same global, provider, agent, and profile tool policy layers used by managed tools.\n- Pass agent/model context into the OpenAI native web-search wrapper and managed `web_search` suppression path.\n- Keep existing global `tools.web.search.enabled` and `tools.web.search.openaiCodex.enabled` behavior unchanged.\n- Add regression coverage for agent deny, session-derived `group:web` deny, provider/model deny, managed-tool suppression parity, and provider payload injection suppression.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/codex-native-web-search.test.ts src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/openai.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner-extraparams.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\n\n## Notes\n\n- Addresses NVIDIA tracking issue https://github.com/NVIDIA-dev/openclaw-tracking/issues/739.\n- This is hardening/policy parity; no `CHANGELOG.md` update.\n",
